wikipedia_page.main: George Moffatt (11 May 1806 – 20 February 1878) was a British Liberal Party politician.He was Member of Parliament (MP) for Dartmouth 1845–52, Ashburton 1852–59, Honiton 1860–65, and  Southampton 1865–68. He subsequently contested the 1870 Isle of Wight by-election, losing by 35 votes.He was also the owner of Goodrich Court, a neo-gothic castle in Herefordshire.
